---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "2026-02-24";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — MinimalDev"
  description="Privacy Policy for MinimalDev. Learn what information may be processed when using the site and how advertising or analytics services may handle data."
  canonicalPath="/legal/privacy-policy/"
>
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="page-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="note">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        MinimalDev provides free online utility tools and informational tool pages.
        This Privacy Policy explains what information may be processed when you use the site,
        what is generally not collected directly by MinimalDev, and how third-party services
        such as advertising or analytics providers may be involved.
      </p>
      <p class="note">
        For most tools, calculations and transformations are designed to run directly in your browser.
        MinimalDev does not require account creation or login for normal use of the site.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Information processed when using tools</h2>
      <p>
        Most tools on MinimalDev are intended to process your inputs locally in the browser.
        In general, values entered into calculators, converters, generators, formatters, and similar tools
        are not intentionally sent to MinimalDev servers as part of normal tool usage.
      </p>
      <p class="note">
        This means that in ordinary use, tool input is primarily handled on your device rather than stored in a user account or submitted through a dedicated backend form.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Information we may collect indirectly</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Basic technical data:</strong> browser type, device type, operating system, referring pages,
          approximate region, and general usage information may be processed by analytics or advertising services if they are enabled.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Site interaction data:</strong> page views, navigation patterns, and general engagement metrics may be measured in aggregated form to understand site usage and improve the service.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="note">
        MinimalDev does not operate a user account database for ordinary visitors and does not ask users to register to access tools.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Information we do not intentionally request for normal tool use</h2>
      <p>
        MinimalDev does not normally require names, account credentials, addresses, payment details,
        or similar personal profile information in order to use the public tools on the site.
      </p>
      <p class="note">
        If you choose to contact the site directly, any information included in your message may be received as part of that communication.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Cookies and advertising</h2>
      <p>
        MinimalDev may use advertising services such as Google AdSense. Third-party vendors, including Google,
        may use cookies or similar identifiers to serve ads based on a user’s visit to this site or other websites.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>You can manage ad personalization through your Google ad settings.</li>
        <li>You can also control or delete cookies through your browser settings.</li>
        <li>Advertising providers may process data according to their own privacy policies and retention practices.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        If analytics tools are used on MinimalDev, they may collect aggregated or pseudonymous data such as page views,
        session information, device categories, approximate location, and general site behavior.
      </p>
      <p class="note">
        This information is used to understand site performance, identify pages that need improvement,
        and maintain the usability of tools and navigation. MinimalDev aims to avoid collecting sensitive personal data through analytics.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        Some services used on the site, including advertising and analytics providers, may process data independently
        under their own terms and privacy policies. MinimalDev does not control how those providers manage all aspects of their systems,
        cookies, or retention schedules.
      </p>
      <p class="note">
        Users should review the privacy materials of relevant third-party providers when they want more detailed information about those services.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        MinimalDev does not maintain a normal user account database for public visitors.
        Where aggregated analytics or advertising-related data exists, storage and retention are generally managed
        by the relevant third-party providers according to their own systems and policies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Children’s privacy</h2>
      <p>
        MinimalDev is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children
        through the normal public use of the site.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time to reflect site changes, service changes,
        or operational updates. The date shown at the top of this page indicates the most recent revision.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p class="note">
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or the way the site operates, please use the
        <a href="/legal/contact/">Contact</a> page.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>